269
00:19:53,735 --> 00:19:56,112
You said you'd get prettier
and here you are.

270
00:19:59,532 --> 00:20:02,744
I got prettier? What is he talking about?

271
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:06,372
I was always pretty.

272
00:20:06,456 --> 00:20:08,207
He just pretended he didn't notice.

273
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:13,546
You don't seem to realize it.

274
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:17,300
Why did he suddenly talk
casually like that?

275
00:20:17,759 --> 00:20:20,845
He's really stirring.

276
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,809
Is he back home safely?

277
00:20:47,455 --> 00:20:49,791
I appreciate the comfortable rides.

278
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:51,084
Thank you.

279
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,850
THE MAN'S HOUSE

280
00:21:14,148 --> 00:21:16,234
"He said I was like a bead."

281
00:21:16,818 --> 00:21:21,072
"That was a praise better suited for
a younger sister than a girlfriend."

282
00:21:21,864 --> 00:21:23,449
"I wasn't satisfied at first,

283
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:26,995
but I began to like that word."

284
00:21:27,870 --> 00:21:31,791
"Beady eyes, beady tears,

285
00:21:31,874 --> 00:21:35,086
beady dews, beady waves."

286
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:38,423
"Wherever the word was
attached, it shone."

287
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:44,637
If someone says this to me,
I will remember it forever too.

288
00:21:47,682 --> 00:21:49,017
"Beady Yu-ri."

289
00:21:51,686 --> 00:21:54,981
I am still keeping things
that I can't throw out.

290
00:21:55,064 --> 00:21:58,484
Because they contain
my own secrets in them.

291
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:09,412
Never forget to take vitamins.

292
00:22:39,776 --> 00:22:42,445
I APPRECIATE THE COMFORTABLE RIDES.
THANK YOU.

293
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:43,946
He's leaving me on read?

294
00:22:49,619 --> 00:22:51,329
Why?

295
00:23:00,213 --> 00:23:04,383
Why men leave you on read.

296
00:23:06,969 --> 00:23:09,680
WHY MEN LEAVE YOU ON READ!
BY DEBORAH

297
00:23:11,516 --> 00:23:14,268
Even when he leaves you on read...

298
00:23:14,352 --> 00:23:16,187
"Does he hate me? Am I dumped?"

299
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:20,233
Don't jump to these conclusions,
staying up all night.

300
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:26,072
He might've been caught up in
unavoidable circumstances.

301
00:23:26,155 --> 00:23:30,952
At the very moment he is about to reply,
his phone may have broken.

302
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:34,789
He may be asleep,
in a fire, in a car accident,

303
00:23:34,872 --> 00:23:37,125
or even dead.

304
00:23:37,834 --> 00:23:42,171
So, don't overreact and say,
"Is there anything wrong?"

305
00:23:42,255 --> 00:23:44,340
It's an obsession disguised as care.

306
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:47,635
You can get ahead of yourself saying,

307
00:23:47,718 --> 00:23:50,596
"You seem to find me uncomfortable.
I won't bother you anymore."

308
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,933
"Isn't it courteous to
reply to a read message?"

309
00:23:54,016 --> 00:23:56,310
Don't be like Confucius and scold harshly.

310
00:23:56,394 --> 00:23:58,729
Just get some sleep

311
00:23:58,813 --> 00:24:01,983
until he tells you what happened.

312
00:24:07,113 --> 00:24:08,239
Right.

313
00:24:08,948 --> 00:24:10,158
Let's sleep.

314
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:20,001
NOH JU-WAN

315
00:24:20,084 --> 00:24:21,169
Are you sleeping?

316
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:30,553
EP 10
CATFISH MAKES WAY, SARDINE MAKES A MOVE

317
00:24:53,409 --> 00:24:57,455
In the past,
Deborah was very active on SNS,

318
00:24:57,538 --> 00:24:58,873
wrote columns and appeared on shows,

319
00:24:58,956 --> 00:25:01,334
so she didn't need
a marketing strategy for promotion.

320
00:25:01,417 --> 00:25:03,878
But she stopped all those activities now.

321
00:25:04,337 --> 00:25:06,422
It's difficult to set up marketing plans.

322
00:25:06,923 --> 00:25:11,093
I agree.
It's best she returns to these activities.

323
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:13,596
However, we can't ask a writer

324
00:25:13,679 --> 00:25:16,307
to do her own promotions.
That's our responsibility.

325
00:25:20,102 --> 00:25:21,062
Su-hyeok.

326
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:23,522
Who says we'll ask her to do
her own promotions?

327
00:25:23,606 --> 00:25:24,815
That's not my point.

328
00:25:24,899 --> 00:25:25,942
Once the book's out,

329
00:25:26,025 --> 00:25:28,236
interviews and book concerts
should follow.

330
00:25:28,611 --> 00:25:31,030
She'll need to
appear before the public anyway.

331
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:35,743
So, maybe she can resume
her activities before publication.

332
00:25:35,826 --> 00:25:38,120
At least we can ask her.

333
00:25:38,204 --> 00:25:40,456
That's the same story after all.

334
00:25:41,165 --> 00:25:44,252
The incident was controversial,
with huge malicious comments.

335
00:25:45,419 --> 00:25:46,879
This cannot be an easy task.

336
00:25:46,963 --> 00:25:50,758
Since you work out with her,
just ask her casually

337
00:25:50,841 --> 00:25:54,637
and persuade her to resume her activities.

338
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:56,722
That's what I meant.

339
00:25:56,806 --> 00:25:57,932
No way.

340
00:25:58,015 --> 00:26:00,017
We don't have that in the contract.

341
00:26:00,101 --> 00:26:01,769
I won't discuss it with her.

342
00:26:01,852 --> 00:26:04,313
-That's it.
-Su-hyeok! Hey!

343
00:26:06,524 --> 00:26:08,150
What's up with him?

344
00:26:09,277 --> 00:26:11,696
Excuse me, Sang-jin.

345
00:26:11,779 --> 00:26:12,780
Yes?

346
00:26:12,863 --> 00:26:17,159
I got paid my first ever salary.

347
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:22,790
Please take a look once I leave.

348
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:37,763
Dear my Daddy-Long-Legs.

349
00:26:37,847 --> 00:26:40,016
As you said you'd accept my heart,

350
00:26:40,099 --> 00:26:41,767
this is my heart.

351
00:26:41,851 --> 00:26:44,353
With love, Judy.

352
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,824
CHATS
NOH JU-WAN

353
00:26:56,907 --> 00:26:57,908
"Are you sleeping?"

354
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:00,286
"Are you sleeping?"

355
00:27:00,369 --> 00:27:02,830
Give it back to me.
Don't press on the message.

356
00:27:04,623 --> 00:27:07,960
Your ex-boyfriend Ju-wan? Why?

357
00:27:08,461 --> 00:27:10,880
He acted as if he would never look back.

358
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:14,091
Did you see this coming, Deborah?

359
00:27:15,301 --> 00:27:19,513
Your ex-boyfriend
will contact you at least once.

360
00:27:19,597 --> 00:27:21,724
For sure, at least once. But...

361
00:27:22,767 --> 00:27:25,895
This is too soon. What does this mean?

362
00:27:25,978 --> 00:27:26,937
What do you think?

363
00:27:28,981 --> 00:27:31,650
What a surprise! Look who it is!

364
00:27:31,734 --> 00:27:34,612
The true lover and macho of our time.

365
00:27:34,695 --> 00:27:37,156
And the terrible son!

366
00:27:38,449 --> 00:27:40,826
Who said women's jealousy is scary?

367
00:27:40,910 --> 00:27:42,578
Oh, my. So scary!

368
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:51,962
What was that? How come he
turned so cold in just one day?

369
00:27:52,338 --> 00:27:55,591
He begged me for a reservation yesterday,
but I refused.

370
00:27:57,635 --> 00:27:59,762
He must've been freaked out.

371
00:28:00,096 --> 00:28:02,348
I know how to play hard to get
and lie too.

372
00:28:04,266 --> 00:28:06,977
Did he lie? About what?

373
00:28:07,061 --> 00:28:08,646
Yesterday, Jin-woo...

374
00:28:11,732 --> 00:28:14,735
Oh, I just found out why Ju-wan
sent you the message.

375
00:28:14,819 --> 00:28:15,653
How is Bo-ra?

376
00:28:16,362 --> 00:28:17,446
Is she doing well?

377
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:18,989
She is.

378
00:28:21,075 --> 00:28:23,202
She seemed to be with someone.

379
00:28:23,285 --> 00:28:24,870
Really? Who?

380
00:28:24,954 --> 00:28:25,788
No idea.

381
00:28:26,705 --> 00:28:28,999
I even saw him on Yu-jeong's Instagram.

382
00:28:29,333 --> 00:28:31,627
That picture with you and the others...

383
00:28:32,211 --> 00:28:34,964
Oh, Lee Su-hyeok?

384
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:37,258
-Is he dating Bo-ra?
-Is he?

385
00:28:37,341 --> 00:28:38,551
You just said so.

386
00:28:41,971 --> 00:28:43,681
I heard they're working together.

387
00:28:44,014 --> 00:28:46,725
But... he came to Bo-ra's place,

388
00:28:46,809 --> 00:28:48,602
and he comes to my bar often, too.

389
00:28:49,687 --> 00:28:51,981
I guess they are seeing each other.

390
00:28:52,773 --> 00:28:54,400
Good for her.

391
00:28:54,483 --> 00:28:55,901
He looks decent.

392
00:28:56,777 --> 00:28:58,237
That's right.

393
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,990
I agree it's good for her.

394
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:03,534
I got it instantly.

395
00:29:03,617 --> 00:29:07,455
Ju-wan is super bothered by Su-hyeok.
It's my hunch.

396
00:29:19,133 --> 00:29:22,845
I feel for him. He's almost crying.
Just forgive him.

397
00:29:23,971 --> 00:29:25,764
He deserved that.

398
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:32,104
Hi, Eun-ju.

399
00:29:33,189 --> 00:29:34,982
Yes, Friday...

400
00:29:35,983 --> 00:29:38,360
I didn't forget. No worries.

401
00:29:39,862 --> 00:29:40,946
Bo-ra?

402
00:29:43,532 --> 00:29:44,742
What about Bo-ra?

403
00:29:45,201 --> 00:29:48,496
I didn't tell Bo-ra.
Make sure you don't either.

404
00:29:49,163 --> 00:29:50,456
Why not?

405
00:29:50,539 --> 00:29:53,834
Because Ju-wan's coming.

406
00:29:54,376 --> 00:29:57,171
I wanted Bo-ra to come.

407
00:29:57,254 --> 00:29:59,882
But my boyfriend is very close to Ju-wan.

408
00:30:00,633 --> 00:30:02,551
And he'll be the MC at my wedding.

409
00:30:03,385 --> 00:30:04,678
Besides...

410
00:30:04,762 --> 00:30:06,222
Among us, you got married and now

411
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:08,432
I'm getting married while Bo-ra is single.

412
00:30:08,516 --> 00:30:11,644
It'd be too mean to ask her to come
to our pre-wedding photo shoot.

413
00:30:12,144 --> 00:30:15,064
What if she curses me
instead of blessing me?

414
00:30:15,147 --> 00:30:19,068
But her viral video is crazy.

415
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:21,403
The group chat exploded!

416
00:30:22,196 --> 00:30:26,242
Actually, even in school,
she was a weirdo.

417
00:30:26,325 --> 00:30:28,327
By the way, is Bo-ra...

418
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:30,788
Hey, Eun-ju, you're on speaker.

419
00:30:30,871 --> 00:30:32,623
Bo-ra's here too. Say hi to her.

420
00:30:32,706 --> 00:30:34,833
Hi, Bo-ra!

421
00:30:34,917 --> 00:30:38,420
How have you been?

422
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:41,006
Hi, Eun-ju! How are you doing?

423
00:30:41,090 --> 00:30:43,133
I am doing excellent.

424
00:30:43,217 --> 00:30:44,969
I was about to call you.

425
00:30:45,052 --> 00:30:47,638
Our pre-wedding photo shoot is on Friday.

426
00:30:48,013 --> 00:30:51,141
I hope that you will be able to join us.

427
00:30:51,225 --> 00:30:52,810
Oh, Friday?

428
00:30:52,893 --> 00:30:55,646
Sorry. I have another appointment
that day.

429
00:30:55,729 --> 00:30:57,398
Busy, right?

430
00:30:57,481 --> 00:30:58,941
I figured.

431
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:01,068
What a busy girl!

432
00:31:01,151 --> 00:31:03,737
You're so successful and famous.

433
00:31:03,821 --> 00:31:05,906
You probably can't come to my wedding.

434
00:31:05,990 --> 00:31:07,741
I will definitely miss you.

435
00:31:07,825 --> 00:31:09,868
Anyway, let's get together someday.

436
00:31:09,952 --> 00:31:11,787
I miss you, Bo-ra!

437
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:14,415
Eun-ju, hold on!

438
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:18,669
Although I have some work to do,
you miss me so much,

439
00:31:18,752 --> 00:31:20,296
so I think I should come.

440
00:31:20,379 --> 00:31:21,589
No, no.

441
00:31:21,672 --> 00:31:23,132
You don't have to.

442
00:31:23,215 --> 00:31:25,009
No, I am okay.

443
00:31:25,092 --> 00:31:27,094
I'll be there. See you then, Eun-ju.

444
00:31:27,177 --> 00:31:28,345
Bye!

445
00:31:31,307 --> 00:31:33,017
Are you really going to go?

446
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:35,644
Are you gonna be okay
with Ju-wan and the others?

447
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:57,499
Hey! You came.

448
00:32:02,504 --> 00:32:04,632
What's up with you? You saw me.

449
00:32:06,133 --> 00:32:07,217
I saw you,

450
00:32:07,676 --> 00:32:09,887
but ignored you. What's wrong with that?

451
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:11,513
It's exactly what you did to me.

452
00:32:11,597 --> 00:32:12,514
What?

453
00:32:16,101 --> 00:32:18,687
Oh, yesterday...

454
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:21,231
I thought about replying.

455
00:32:21,857 --> 00:32:25,235
But I had nothing to say,
and it wasn't a question either...

456
00:32:27,613 --> 00:32:30,449
You won't reply unless I ask a question?

457
00:32:33,410 --> 00:32:36,914
You were disappointed, weren't you?
Did you wait for my reply?

458
00:32:38,374 --> 00:32:41,001
You could've just called me.

459
00:32:41,085 --> 00:32:42,586
That's not a big deal.

460
00:32:42,670 --> 00:32:44,755
I didn't say that. The fact is...

461
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:47,841
I'm upset about being left on read.

462
00:32:47,925 --> 00:32:50,594
Instead of leaving it on read,
just pretend you never read it.

463
00:32:52,388 --> 00:32:53,222
Or...

464
00:32:54,223 --> 00:32:55,391
Just as I did,

465
00:32:57,267 --> 00:32:59,353
don't press read and just ignore it.

466
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:04,566
What? "Are you sleeping?"

467
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:07,111
-What's this?
-Did you see it?

468
00:33:07,194 --> 00:33:08,529
You showed it to me.

469
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,366
What do you think it is?
You'd know since you're a guy.

470
00:33:12,449 --> 00:33:14,243
It's the typical text from your ex.

471
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:17,871
"Are you sleeping?" "What are you doing?"
You know what they mean.

472
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:20,958
Yes, I know it well.

473
00:33:21,041 --> 00:33:22,376
They are all meaningless.

474
00:33:25,629 --> 00:33:26,922
Why didn't you reply then?

475
00:33:28,841 --> 00:33:30,300
Because...

476
00:33:31,051 --> 00:33:32,845
I chose to do nothing.

477
00:33:35,097 --> 00:33:37,182
Yeah. Well done.

478
00:33:37,933 --> 00:33:39,351
Don't reply to him.

479
00:33:39,435 --> 00:33:42,062
If it's bothersome, just block him.

480
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:49,737
But I have a problem.

481
00:33:49,820 --> 00:33:51,405
This coming Friday,

482
00:33:51,488 --> 00:33:56,493
a couple I'm close to
will have a pre-wedding photo shoot.

483
00:33:56,577 --> 00:34:00,289
All our friends will come there
including Ju-wan.

484
00:34:01,123 --> 00:34:02,666
What should I do?

485
00:34:05,502 --> 00:34:07,171
Why are you concerned?

486
00:34:07,254 --> 00:34:08,797
Just say you will not go.

487
00:34:12,634 --> 00:34:14,261
-Why should I?
-Why?

488
00:34:16,430 --> 00:34:18,682
Do you wanna ruin their day of happiness?

489
00:34:19,016 --> 00:34:21,810
A broken-up couple could make
them uncomfortable.

490
00:34:21,894 --> 00:34:23,854
You should know better.

491
00:34:23,937 --> 00:34:25,898
How dare you go there?

492
00:34:25,981 --> 00:34:27,399
Besides...

493
00:34:27,483 --> 00:34:28,859
Don't forget our plan.

494
00:34:29,234 --> 00:34:31,403
Do nothing and get prettier.

495
00:34:32,196 --> 00:34:35,282
You can't just show up there
in this condition.

496
00:34:36,033 --> 00:34:37,284
"This condition"?

497
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:40,829
Didn't you say I got prettier?

498
00:34:41,330 --> 00:34:44,833
I said it only to motivate you.

499
00:34:44,917 --> 00:34:46,376
If you show up like this,

500
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:48,921
you will make him wonder
if you want him back

501
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:51,465
or if you wanna cut the cord completely.

502
00:34:52,216 --> 00:34:53,342
Absolutely not.

503
00:34:57,429 --> 00:34:59,264
What can I do then?

504
00:34:59,348 --> 00:35:01,391
I told her I would come no matter what.

505
00:35:01,892 --> 00:35:03,519
Should I go to cut the cord?

506
00:35:14,154 --> 00:35:16,865
So, you're going to go no matter what?

507
00:35:19,243 --> 00:35:21,829
I am concerned you're gonna mess up again.

508
00:35:24,790 --> 00:35:27,960
Because scandals tend to follow you.

509
00:35:29,628 --> 00:35:32,589
Who knows? I might just keep talking
to feel less awkward,

510
00:35:32,673 --> 00:35:35,926
or just get drunk and fall,
talking bullshit.

511
00:35:36,009 --> 00:35:37,678
Whatever. Why?

512
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,514
Is that confusing you? "Are you sleeping?"

513
00:35:42,474 --> 00:35:43,976
It doesn't mean anything.

514
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:46,645
-Men tend to...
-I know.

515
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:48,272
That means nothing.

516
00:35:49,314 --> 00:35:51,316
It's just a kind of catfish effect.

517
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:53,068
Catfish effect?

518
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:56,405
I heard he asked about you, Su-hyeok.

519
00:35:57,239 --> 00:35:59,324
And then, he messaged me out of nowhere.

520
00:36:02,494 --> 00:36:05,747
Oh, you're saying I am a catfish?

521
00:36:05,831 --> 00:36:07,332
Look out!

522
00:36:13,672 --> 00:36:14,798
Are you okay?

523
00:36:15,424 --> 00:36:16,758
I tried to protect you.

524
00:36:17,426 --> 00:36:18,677
Not intentional?

525
00:36:21,889 --> 00:36:23,515
Your things got scattered.

526
00:36:23,599 --> 00:36:26,810
Why do you carry garbage in you car?

527
00:36:26,894 --> 00:36:28,729
Do you want me to throw them out later?

528
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:30,314
Leave them there.

529
00:36:32,858 --> 00:36:35,694
Can I have this one?

530
00:36:35,777 --> 00:36:37,613
-Is it fun?
-Just leave it there.

531
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:44,286
It's no fun.

532
00:37:02,179 --> 00:37:04,139
-Good night.
-See you.

533
00:37:16,735 --> 00:37:19,613
Why is he so serious about it?

534
00:37:20,322 --> 00:37:21,615
Still not over her?

535
00:37:22,866 --> 00:37:25,953
Why does he still
carry them around in his car?

536
00:37:33,543 --> 00:37:35,087
I can't help it.

537
00:37:37,506 --> 00:37:41,385
Let me read it and totally ignore it.

538
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:45,555
What does it mean?

539
00:37:49,559 --> 00:37:51,019
"I can't help it."

540
00:37:53,271 --> 00:37:54,731
"I can't help confessing?"

541
00:37:55,065 --> 00:37:56,775
"I can't help wanting you and only you."

542
00:37:56,858 --> 00:37:59,319
"I can't help thinking about you."

543
00:38:03,365 --> 00:38:06,868
JINLEE PUBLISHING LEE SU-HYEOK

544
00:38:08,996 --> 00:38:10,038
Hello.

545
00:38:10,122 --> 00:38:11,415
Why aren't you replying?

546
00:38:11,832 --> 00:38:14,084
I left you on read. Don't expect my reply.

547
00:38:15,335 --> 00:38:17,045
You can't help what?

548
00:38:18,088 --> 00:38:21,091
I can't help it.
I can't let you go there alone.

549
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:22,801
So...

550
00:38:22,884 --> 00:38:24,219
Don't go there?

551
00:38:25,804 --> 00:38:26,680
Let me go with you.

552
00:38:28,598 --> 00:38:30,976
Why do you wanna go there?

553
00:38:31,476 --> 00:38:33,061
You talked about catfish effect.

554
00:38:33,145 --> 00:38:35,313
Let me be the catfish you need.

555
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,734
The more I provoke him,

556
00:38:38,817 --> 00:38:40,360
greater the effect.

557
00:38:40,444 --> 00:38:43,113
So you're gonna act like my boyfriend?

558
00:38:43,947 --> 00:38:45,240
That's it!

559
00:38:45,782 --> 00:38:47,034
So, just use me.

560
00:38:52,456 --> 00:38:53,623
Good night.

561
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:59,671
Why is he so excited?

562
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:02,632
And so enthusiastic.

563
00:39:05,635 --> 00:39:07,095
How impatient.

564
00:39:08,263 --> 00:39:09,681
"I'll buy you coffee next time."

565
00:39:09,765 --> 00:39:11,892
That's the last thing you said to me.

566
00:39:11,975 --> 00:39:13,810
So when are you buying me coffee?

567
00:39:13,894 --> 00:39:15,145
How about tomorrow?

568
00:39:17,272 --> 00:39:18,690
Let's go, let's go, Korea!

569
00:39:20,317 --> 00:39:21,902
Let's go, let's go, Korea!

570
00:39:23,278 --> 00:39:24,613
Let's go, let's go, Korea!

571
00:39:24,696 --> 00:39:27,115
Are you with the Red Devils or what?

572
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:28,408
Did you lose a bet?

573
00:39:29,326 --> 00:39:30,869
You got terrible taste.

574
00:39:30,952 --> 00:39:33,872
Doesn't it look nice?
It makes my face look lively.

575
00:39:34,331 --> 00:39:36,416
I am into the color red now.

576
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:40,879
What do you think, U-ri? Looking good?

577
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:42,923
You look awesome in it!

578
00:39:43,006 --> 00:39:43,840
Right, U-ri.

579
00:39:43,924 --> 00:39:47,177
Only a few can look awesome in this color.

580
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:48,845
How funny.

581
00:40:00,482 --> 00:40:01,691
Bo-ra!

582
00:40:01,775 --> 00:40:03,819
Oh, my.

583
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:05,237
It's been a while!

584
00:40:05,612 --> 00:40:07,030
How serious is it?

585
00:40:07,114 --> 00:40:09,282
Nothing serious. I'll be okay soon.

586
00:40:09,366 --> 00:40:11,076
Long time no see!

587
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:12,202
You got prettier.

588
00:40:12,285 --> 00:40:13,453
How dare you!

589
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:16,581
I caused damage to the show.

590
00:40:16,665 --> 00:40:18,792
I was so sorry that
I couldn't even call you.

591
00:40:18,875 --> 00:40:20,752
That's why I called first.

592
00:40:21,586 --> 00:40:23,630
Not because we wanted your apology.

593
00:40:23,713 --> 00:40:26,091
Did you listen to our program lately?

594
00:40:28,552 --> 00:40:30,720
I was too upset to listen to it.

595
00:40:31,888 --> 00:40:34,850
Then, I guess you didn't know
we never found a replacement.

596
00:40:36,268 --> 00:40:38,562
We once considered
getting rid of the segment.

597
00:40:38,645 --> 00:40:40,856
We have guest hosts for now.

598
00:40:40,939 --> 00:40:42,899
So, when will you return?

599
00:40:44,651 --> 00:40:45,652
Me?

600
00:40:50,907 --> 00:40:54,411
Don't think too much,
but seriously consider it.

601
00:40:54,494 --> 00:40:57,622
-I will.
-Okay.

602
00:40:57,706 --> 00:40:59,541
We can't wait too long.

603
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:02,460
Yes, ma'am.

604
00:41:02,544 --> 00:41:03,795
See you.

605
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:17,809
Bo-ra.

606
00:41:18,435 --> 00:41:19,936
Oh, Yu-ri.

607
00:41:21,813 --> 00:41:24,858
I'd like to give you this.

608
00:41:29,404 --> 00:41:31,448
Are you getting married?

609
00:41:32,908 --> 00:41:34,659
How pretty!

610
00:41:36,745 --> 00:41:41,249
When people hand me an invitation,
they are scared that I will curse them.

611
00:41:42,292 --> 00:41:44,961
I appreciate your courage.
I will attend your wedding.

612
00:41:45,045 --> 00:41:46,671
I would appreciate it.

613
00:41:48,924 --> 00:41:51,009
I have something else to thank you for.

614
00:41:53,053 --> 00:41:57,307
When I decided on my marriage,
"Deborah says!" played a decisive role.

615
00:41:58,099 --> 00:42:00,352
Do you happen to remember the story

616
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:03,939
about a relationship with a man
who never confesses his feelings?

617
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:05,982
That was my story.

618
00:42:09,611 --> 00:42:13,031
I was confused between two men,

619
00:42:13,114 --> 00:42:14,991
one who never confesses

620
00:42:15,075 --> 00:42:16,993
and one who gave me a sense of trust.

621
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:20,163
The moment I listened to
"Deborah says!", I woke up.

622
00:42:23,625 --> 00:42:24,668
Then...

623
00:42:26,211 --> 00:42:27,420
This invitation is...

624
00:42:27,879 --> 00:42:29,130
Yes, you're right.

625
00:42:29,214 --> 00:42:31,925
For marrying the man
who gives me a sense of trust.

626
00:42:32,008 --> 00:42:33,802
It's kind of a happy ending.

627
00:42:34,261 --> 00:42:36,346
Congrats!

628
00:42:37,055 --> 00:42:39,015
I am glad I was helpful.

629
00:42:39,099 --> 00:42:42,018
Not just helpful, but decisive.

630
00:42:43,270 --> 00:42:48,441
So, I thought I would give
the first invitation to my ex.

631
00:42:48,525 --> 00:42:51,152
But as I met you today
I wanted to give it to you first.

632
00:42:51,695 --> 00:42:55,865
Dumping a wedding invitation
on an ex-boyfriend?

633
00:42:56,825 --> 00:43:00,453
Yu-ri, I never thought you were
such a scary person.

634
00:43:01,621 --> 00:43:04,374
By the way, you like this book, too?

635
00:43:06,126 --> 00:43:09,462
I can't say I like it yet.
I haven't read half of it.

636
00:43:10,630 --> 00:43:12,549
This is my favorite book.

637
00:43:13,508 --> 00:43:15,135
You know, there are books like that.

638
00:43:15,218 --> 00:43:20,515
You don't want to just borrow it from
a library, but have it on your bookshelf

639
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:22,892
to read it whenever you like.

640
00:43:22,976 --> 00:43:24,686
Each reading feels different.

641
00:43:26,062 --> 00:43:29,399
So this book is that kind of book.

642
00:43:29,482 --> 00:43:32,527
Someone told me straight out
this book was no fun.

643
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:34,529
I wondered if I should read it.

644
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:38,825
What? It can't be.

645
00:43:38,908 --> 00:43:39,951
Who told you so?

646
00:43:40,869 --> 00:43:42,871
Someone.

647
00:43:43,413 --> 00:43:45,498
He tells a joke keeping a straight face.

648
00:43:45,582 --> 00:43:47,792
He seldom grins.

649
00:43:47,876 --> 00:43:50,253
Unless I send a question,
he never replies.

650
00:43:50,337 --> 00:43:54,799
And he replies with "maybe," "probably,"
or "likely" and so on.

651
00:43:58,720 --> 00:44:01,264
That reminds me of a man.

652
00:44:02,182 --> 00:44:03,058
So...

653
00:44:03,558 --> 00:44:05,352
What is the book like these days?

654
00:44:06,478 --> 00:44:07,937
Currently...

655
00:44:10,940 --> 00:44:12,650
As it is in this book,

656
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:19,074
I wish when I show him the invitation,
he would cry very hard.

657
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,827
I wish he would collapse into my arms.

658
00:44:24,329 --> 00:44:26,456
I wish while I live a happy life,

659
00:44:26,539 --> 00:44:30,960
he would stay there forever
getting blind gradually,

660
00:44:31,586 --> 00:44:33,713
waiting for me forever.

661
00:44:36,758 --> 00:44:40,845
That's my innermost feeling
that I want to hide.

662
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,853
That sounds scarier than that
famous line, "I will destroy you."

663
00:44:48,937 --> 00:44:49,938
What is it?

664
00:44:50,021 --> 00:44:54,109
Revenge? Or lingering feelings?

665
00:44:54,818 --> 00:44:55,944
Not sure.

666
00:44:56,820 --> 00:44:59,364
I though there was nothing left at all.

667
00:45:00,115 --> 00:45:05,829
I guess I wanna shake him up
one last time to check if there is.

668
00:45:05,912 --> 00:45:08,081
I may still have such desire.

669
00:45:12,669 --> 00:45:16,548
KANG SANG-JUN, LIM YU-RI

670
00:45:18,633 --> 00:45:20,802
This is not a genuine invitation.

671
00:45:23,096 --> 00:45:25,098
You would've found out anyway.

672
00:45:25,723 --> 00:45:28,309
But I didn't want you
to hear it from others.

673
00:45:32,397 --> 00:45:34,774
So I decided to let you know myself.

674
00:45:46,536 --> 00:45:47,579
I got it.

675
00:45:48,955 --> 00:45:49,998
Congrats.

676
00:45:55,044 --> 00:45:56,546
And back then...

677
00:45:59,257 --> 00:46:01,342
I am sorry I was too harsh on you.

678
00:46:02,177 --> 00:46:03,928
I didn't mean what I said.

679
00:46:04,637 --> 00:46:06,764
I was grateful to you for many things.

680
00:46:09,142 --> 00:46:11,060
We had wonderful times, too.

681
00:46:12,604 --> 00:46:15,440
But I...

682
00:46:18,443 --> 00:46:19,652
Don't be.

683
00:46:20,278 --> 00:46:21,571
I was sorry too.

684
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:28,244
After we broke up, I regretted
not making good memories together

685
00:46:30,747 --> 00:46:33,166
and just spending time drinking.

686
00:46:36,377 --> 00:46:38,338
I should've treated you better.

687
00:46:42,759 --> 00:46:46,596
I'm also sorry I didn't notice
you were having a hard time.

688
00:47:01,945 --> 00:47:03,071
How is he?

689
00:47:05,323 --> 00:47:06,658
Does he treat you well?

690
00:47:08,952 --> 00:47:09,869
Yes.

691
00:47:10,745 --> 00:47:11,829
He is a good man.

692
00:47:15,333 --> 00:47:20,505
What I was eager for
and what you had a hard time doing,

693
00:47:22,757 --> 00:47:24,842
he can provide them easily.

694
00:47:25,927 --> 00:47:27,428
He loves me a lot.

695
00:47:28,263 --> 00:47:30,390
I can notice it without asking him.

696
00:47:32,350 --> 00:47:33,935
So I feel comfortable with him.

697
00:47:35,103 --> 00:47:36,354
Everything is good.

698
00:47:40,650 --> 00:47:41,651
Good for you.

699
00:47:45,572 --> 00:47:47,532
Everything worked out well.

700
00:47:56,708 --> 00:48:00,169
I must sound funny if I ask this.

701
00:48:03,423 --> 00:48:04,882
But it's important to me.

702
00:48:10,305 --> 00:48:12,599
Did you really love me?

703
00:48:23,610 --> 00:48:24,777
Why can't you answer?

704
00:48:28,865 --> 00:48:31,075
Did I mean anything to you?

705
00:48:32,076 --> 00:48:34,162
A girl you slept with and had fun with?

706
00:48:34,579 --> 00:48:37,540
A comfortable and easy girl?

707
00:48:38,916 --> 00:48:40,376
-Yu-ri.
-So...

708
00:48:41,044 --> 00:48:44,547
did you never regret our breakup?

709
00:48:49,886 --> 00:48:52,972
I am not sure what you
want to hear from me.

710
00:48:54,724 --> 00:48:56,267
But I have nothing to say.

711
00:48:57,894 --> 00:48:59,437
We're done for good.

712
00:49:01,648 --> 00:49:06,027
Even if we got hurt from each other,
arguing about it, apologizing for it

713
00:49:06,110 --> 00:49:07,320
and regretting it...

714
00:49:10,114 --> 00:49:11,407
Everything's meaningless.

715
00:49:16,954 --> 00:49:18,873
-So...
-I changed my mind.

716
00:49:21,084 --> 00:49:22,335
Come to my wedding.

717
00:49:24,295 --> 00:49:25,546
Come and see

718
00:49:26,756 --> 00:49:28,508
how happy I am,

719
00:49:30,551 --> 00:49:32,303
and what chance you missed.

720
00:50:23,896 --> 00:50:25,064
What are you doing alone?

721
00:50:29,360 --> 00:50:31,112
I just wanted to be alone.

722
00:50:32,113 --> 00:50:34,157
By the way, Mr. Han called to see me.

723
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:36,117
So, I am on the way to his company.

724
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:38,161
Let me buy some coffee.

725
00:50:38,244 --> 00:50:39,579
I hope everyone's there.

726
00:50:39,662 --> 00:50:41,038
How many cups should I buy?

727
00:50:43,750 --> 00:50:45,209
Ms. Yeon, I'm really sorry.

728
00:50:45,293 --> 00:50:47,086
I need to check on something today.

729
00:50:47,170 --> 00:50:48,796
Let's reschedule our appointment.

730
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:52,091
But he has some other business
to attend to.

731
00:50:52,592 --> 00:50:53,801
Money saved.

732
00:50:56,095 --> 00:50:57,221
What's this?

733
00:51:01,851 --> 00:51:03,561
Do you know Yu-ri?

734
00:51:16,616 --> 00:51:17,867
Can I have this one?

735
00:51:17,950 --> 00:51:19,160
Just leave it there.

736
00:51:20,953 --> 00:51:22,538
By the way, you like this book, too?

737
00:51:22,622 --> 00:51:24,332
This is my favorite book.

738
00:51:24,415 --> 00:51:27,919
I thought I would give
the first invitation to my ex.

739
00:51:37,637 --> 00:51:40,431
So, you are...

740
00:51:41,265 --> 00:51:43,559
Yu-ri's ex-boyfriend?

741
00:51:52,777 --> 00:51:56,906
DEEP HOUSE
DRINK FROM DAY TO NIGHT

742
00:51:56,989 --> 00:51:58,574
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

743
00:52:00,743 --> 00:52:02,036
Here.

744
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:03,120
Here you go.

745
00:52:03,204 --> 00:52:05,748
Why should I drink in daylight?

746
00:52:07,625 --> 00:52:11,712
Your ex-girlfriend handed
a wedding invitation to you.

747
00:52:13,214 --> 00:52:14,715
Coffee would taste too bitter.

748
00:52:15,967 --> 00:52:17,218
What about soju then?

749
00:52:21,347 --> 00:52:22,557
Is it bitter?

750
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:25,560
If soju tastes bitter, we can add beer.

751
00:52:27,770 --> 00:52:28,813
I just...

752
00:52:30,481 --> 00:52:31,941
want to console you.

753
00:52:33,943 --> 00:52:34,777
Cheers!

754
00:53:07,518 --> 00:53:09,145
Then, why did we get divorced?

755
00:53:10,730 --> 00:53:12,106
You haven't answered yet.

756
00:53:16,235 --> 00:53:17,653
We used to get along well.

757
00:53:18,112 --> 00:53:19,906
No big fights either.

758
00:53:19,989 --> 00:53:21,490
We got along well?

759
00:53:22,742 --> 00:53:24,285
Because we didn't fight?

760
00:53:25,453 --> 00:53:27,455
Did we have time to fight face-to-face?

761
00:53:28,247 --> 00:53:29,624
That's because...

762
00:53:30,416 --> 00:53:32,251
Then, I had to focus on the company.

763
00:53:32,335 --> 00:53:34,086
We both were busy.

764
00:53:34,670 --> 00:53:37,340
But I don't think
that's the reason for our divorce.

765
00:53:38,758 --> 00:53:41,844
When we got back from my parents',
you suddenly asked for a divorce.

766
00:53:41,928 --> 00:53:42,762
That's why...

767
00:53:45,598 --> 00:53:47,558
I thought that's the reason
for our divorce.

768
00:53:47,642 --> 00:53:49,810
But you say it's not. Then what is it?

769
00:53:56,525 --> 00:53:57,944
I have a question.

770
00:53:59,278 --> 00:54:01,155
"Did you really love me?"

771
00:54:03,074 --> 00:54:05,743
What does this question mean?

772
00:54:09,288 --> 00:54:13,626
The answer determines
whether it's a good memory, a scar,

773
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:17,964
a lingering old love,
or a bitter past you want to forget.

774
00:54:21,384 --> 00:54:22,426
By the way,

775
00:54:23,219 --> 00:54:24,595
what was your answer?

776
00:54:26,847 --> 00:54:28,849
I said, "We're done for good.

777
00:54:30,476 --> 00:54:32,228
"Everything's meaningless."

778
00:54:34,647 --> 00:54:37,817
Why? Was I wrong again?

779
00:54:38,401 --> 00:54:40,987
They call it Zeigarnik effect.

780
00:54:41,570 --> 00:54:44,448
It's unanswered,
so it lingers within you longer.

781
00:54:44,907 --> 00:54:48,995
Because she didn't get an answer from you,
she can't forget about it.

782
00:55:00,339 --> 00:55:01,841
The reason for our divorce?

783
00:55:03,884 --> 00:55:05,511
Because we didn't love each other.

784
00:55:06,470 --> 00:55:08,264
I realized it on that day.

785
00:55:08,681 --> 00:55:10,725
I was there for the memorial service.

786
00:55:10,808 --> 00:55:13,185
With your relatives,
we were eating facing each other.

787
00:55:13,269 --> 00:55:14,812
At the moment, I realized that

788
00:55:15,438 --> 00:55:19,066
we hadn't eaten together in two weeks.

789
00:55:20,276 --> 00:55:21,777
"Are you busy these days?"

790
00:55:21,861 --> 00:55:24,071
"Yes. It's him that I am concerned about."

791
00:55:24,155 --> 00:55:25,531
"Any plans for a baby?"

792
00:55:25,614 --> 00:55:28,534
"Maybe next year."
Sitting there laughing...

793
00:55:29,201 --> 00:55:32,747
and just pretending like
nothing was wrong.

794
00:55:34,457 --> 00:55:36,125
I couldn't stand it anymore.

795
00:55:37,710 --> 00:55:39,962
After we came back home,

796
00:55:40,046 --> 00:55:41,839
I told you that I wanted change

797
00:55:42,631 --> 00:55:44,550
and said we should make effort.

798
00:55:46,844 --> 00:55:49,180
But you said you didn't love me.

799
00:55:52,725 --> 00:55:54,643
Did I? When?

800
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:56,645
I didn't say that.

801
00:55:57,897 --> 00:56:00,399
You did. Clearly.

802
00:56:07,073 --> 00:56:09,825
So what do you want me to do?

803
00:56:13,579 --> 00:56:14,914
What do you want to do?

804
00:56:16,707 --> 00:56:18,000
I'll do as you say.

805
00:56:23,839 --> 00:56:24,924
I want a divorce.

806
00:56:30,846 --> 00:56:32,807
Okay. Let's do it.

807
00:56:34,809 --> 00:56:39,105
And I realized
that you had been waiting...

808
00:56:39,688 --> 00:56:42,942
"You say it, you say it."

809
00:56:45,069 --> 00:56:47,113
You were waiting for me to say it.

810
00:56:49,365 --> 00:56:52,535
What are you talking about?

811
00:56:52,618 --> 00:56:54,453
When did I say that?

812
00:56:54,537 --> 00:56:56,455
Don't make excuses. It's too late.

813
00:57:06,549 --> 00:57:08,843
Let me take you home today.

814
00:57:11,637 --> 00:57:12,763
No thanks.

815
00:57:14,640 --> 00:57:17,226
Let's say bye here.

816
00:57:19,687 --> 00:57:21,313
I want to walk a bit.

817
00:57:23,691 --> 00:57:25,025
You do?

818
00:57:29,864 --> 00:57:31,031
Okay, then.

819
00:58:09,820 --> 00:58:12,323
Don't just send money. You should come.

820
00:58:13,991 --> 00:58:16,243
In return, I will attend
your second wedding.

821
00:58:20,206 --> 00:58:22,791
By the way, where is Su-hyeok?

822
00:58:23,500 --> 00:58:24,335
Why?

823
00:58:24,960 --> 00:58:26,712
You're gonna give it to Su-hyeok?

824
00:58:27,421 --> 00:58:29,465
I gave it to him already.

825
00:58:30,799 --> 00:58:33,260
And to Su-jin, too.

826
00:58:33,344 --> 00:58:38,224
Now that I'm closer to her than you,
I had to invite her too.

827
00:58:39,141 --> 00:58:42,311
So, you guys talk and decide
who is coming.

828
00:58:45,064 --> 00:58:46,023
Okay.

829
00:58:46,607 --> 00:58:47,441
Well done.

830
00:58:49,318 --> 00:58:52,446
You know Deborah, the writer, don't you?
She hosted your radio show.

831
00:58:53,489 --> 00:58:54,657
Very well.

832
00:58:54,740 --> 00:58:57,576
I met her to ask her
to return to the show.

833
00:58:57,660 --> 00:58:59,245
Did you?

834
00:58:59,912 --> 00:59:03,457
We're working on Deborah's new book.

835
00:59:08,671 --> 00:59:11,465
Then, is Su-hyeok working on it?

836
00:59:13,300 --> 00:59:14,343
Yeah.

837
00:59:20,266 --> 00:59:22,810
Someone told me straight out
this book was no fun.

838
00:59:22,893 --> 00:59:24,979
I wondered if I should read it.

839
00:59:25,604 --> 00:59:26,480
Who told you so?

840
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:27,898
Someone.

841
00:59:27,982 --> 00:59:30,276
He tells a joke keeping a straight face.

842
00:59:30,359 --> 00:59:31,902
He seldom grins.

843
00:59:32,778 --> 00:59:35,197
Unless I send a question,
he never replies.

844
00:59:35,281 --> 00:59:39,910
And he replies with "maybe," "probably,"
or "likely" and so on.

845
00:59:51,297 --> 00:59:52,589
Bo-ra.

846
00:59:54,216 --> 00:59:55,092
Hi, Yu-ri.

847
00:59:57,303 --> 00:59:59,722
You're visiting Jinlee Publishing?

848
00:59:59,805 --> 01:00:02,141
Well... Yes.

849
01:00:02,933 --> 01:00:04,268
What brought you here?

850
01:00:05,311 --> 01:00:07,354
I was here to see someone.

851
01:00:08,647 --> 01:00:10,274
Go ahead now.

852
01:00:10,357 --> 01:00:11,191
Okay.

853
01:00:17,865 --> 01:00:18,991
Yu-ri.

854
01:00:24,455 --> 01:00:25,706
By the way...

855
01:00:26,540 --> 01:00:28,751
You asked the wrong question.

856
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:30,669
What?

857
01:00:31,211 --> 01:00:34,631
You should've asked me
whether to choose a man

858
01:00:34,715 --> 01:00:37,009
who never confesses his feelings

859
01:00:37,092 --> 01:00:39,178
or a man who gave you a sense of trust.

860
01:00:39,970 --> 01:00:41,680
But you didn't ask me like that.

861
01:00:43,098 --> 01:00:45,976
I was about to tell you that.

862
01:00:47,853 --> 01:00:49,813
You lied by not telling me.

863
01:00:49,897 --> 01:00:52,858
Lies mixed with truth could be
more dangerous.

864
01:00:53,484 --> 01:00:55,486
You can deceive your partner and others.

865
01:00:55,569 --> 01:00:57,279
But you must've known yourself

866
01:00:58,113 --> 01:01:00,324
whether you're cheating, two-timing,

867
01:01:00,949 --> 01:01:02,117
or moving on right away.

868
01:01:03,243 --> 01:01:07,081
And how unfair and petty you were.

869
01:01:08,165 --> 01:01:08,999
Am I right?

870
01:01:11,126 --> 01:01:12,169
You are.

871
01:01:15,589 --> 01:01:16,590
But...

872
01:01:18,175 --> 01:01:22,679
Relationships are meant to be
petty and unfair.

873
01:01:27,768 --> 01:01:28,769
So petty.

874
01:01:28,852 --> 01:01:32,481
Relationships are meant to be
petty and unfair.

875
01:01:38,779 --> 01:01:43,283
I myself am thinking about the offer
to return to the show.

876
01:01:43,367 --> 01:01:45,702
Are you? Oh, mine!

877
01:01:45,786 --> 01:01:48,038
Even you're trying to
come up with something.

878
01:01:48,831 --> 01:01:52,292
He told me we shouldn't ask a writer
to do her own promotions.

879
01:01:53,752 --> 01:01:54,753
What?

880
01:01:54,837 --> 01:01:56,296
It's Su-hyeok.

881
01:01:56,755 --> 01:01:58,424
He didn't wanna burden you.

882
01:01:58,507 --> 01:02:01,093
So he refused to talk to you about it.

883
01:02:07,349 --> 01:02:10,310
Where is Su-hyeok anyway?

884
01:02:10,394 --> 01:02:12,896
He took a day off, which is unusual.

885
01:02:14,022 --> 01:02:16,275
He is not in good shape these days.

886
01:02:25,409 --> 01:02:27,703
What? He didn't even come to work.

887
01:02:33,792 --> 01:02:36,378
I dropped by, but you're not here.

888
01:02:36,462 --> 01:02:38,422
Are you very sick?

889
01:03:09,703 --> 01:03:11,497
Are you eating well?

890
01:03:11,580 --> 01:03:14,458
You're not drinking
and crying alone, are you?

891
01:03:14,541 --> 01:03:16,460
I don't have to worry about you, do I?

892
01:03:16,543 --> 01:03:18,795
You're not jumping
in front of cars, are you?

893
01:03:18,879 --> 01:03:21,006
Why are you not replying?

894
01:03:21,089 --> 01:03:23,717
I'm not supposed to get upset now, right?

895
01:03:25,010 --> 01:03:28,931
Let me know anytime
when you need a free hug.

896
01:03:29,014 --> 01:03:32,226
And this is not a question.

897
01:03:32,309 --> 01:03:33,852
You don't need to reply.

898
01:03:45,656 --> 01:03:46,657
What?

899
01:03:47,574 --> 01:03:48,617
Hello.

900
01:03:48,700 --> 01:03:50,077
What are you doing?

901
01:03:50,160 --> 01:03:51,328
What am I doing?

902
01:03:51,411 --> 01:03:53,747
I'm going to the pre-wedding photo shoot.

903
01:03:53,830 --> 01:03:55,040
With whom?

904
01:03:55,707 --> 01:03:57,626
Someone is supposed to go with me.

905
01:03:57,709 --> 01:03:59,670
He didn't show up. I'm going alone.

906
01:04:03,048 --> 01:04:04,174
What the heck?

907
01:04:05,384 --> 01:04:07,469
Why are you so late? I waited for a while.

908
01:04:07,970 --> 01:04:11,348
I thought you forgot.
Are you really going with me?

909
01:04:11,431 --> 01:04:14,309
I told you. You can use me.

910
01:04:16,228 --> 01:04:19,231
You should've called.
Thank you for the ride.

911
01:04:27,698 --> 01:04:30,242
-Can I drink this?
-Sure.

912
01:04:32,411 --> 01:04:33,829
Are you okay?

913
01:04:33,912 --> 01:04:36,832
There are some tissues inside.

914
01:04:57,936 --> 01:05:00,188
YU-RI

915
01:05:18,373 --> 01:05:20,834
YU-RI

916
01:05:29,676 --> 01:05:30,677
Su-hyeok.

917
01:05:33,847 --> 01:05:38,727
I am at the place in front of your place

918
01:05:38,810 --> 01:05:40,270
where we met every day.

919
01:05:41,772 --> 01:05:43,774
So what?

920
01:05:46,193 --> 01:05:47,527
I just miss you.

921
01:05:50,739 --> 01:05:52,157
What should I do?

922
01:05:53,158 --> 01:05:55,118
I can't do this, Su-hyeok.

923
01:05:57,245 --> 01:05:58,872
Can you let me go like this?

924
01:05:58,955 --> 01:06:00,832
Can I just leave like this?

925
01:06:02,709 --> 01:06:04,169
Are you sure you're okay?

926
01:06:07,255 --> 01:06:09,591
I can't do this.

927
01:06:09,675 --> 01:06:10,550
Yu-ri.

928
01:06:12,094 --> 01:06:13,762
I'll call later...

929
01:06:13,845 --> 01:06:15,639
Can you come here right now?

930
01:06:20,394 --> 01:06:21,853
I miss you, Su-hyeok.

931
01:06:53,844 --> 01:06:54,803
I'm sorry.

932
01:06:57,556 --> 01:06:59,391
I need to drop by somewhere.

933
01:07:00,726 --> 01:07:02,310
I can't go with you.

934
01:07:03,812 --> 01:07:05,814
What?

935
01:07:16,366 --> 01:07:18,535
Do you really have to go?

936
01:08:04,915 --> 01:08:06,750
I wish while I live a happy life,

937
01:08:07,167 --> 01:08:11,546
he would stay there forever
getting blind gradually,

938
01:08:12,088 --> 01:08:14,257
waiting for me forever.

939
01:08:15,258 --> 01:08:18,178
I though there was nothing left at all.

940
01:08:18,261 --> 01:08:23,475
Maybe I wanted to
shake him up one last time.

941
01:08:24,100 --> 01:08:26,353
I may still have such a desire.

942
01:08:49,835 --> 01:08:54,506
The catfish begins to make way,
so the sardine begins to make a move.

943
01:09:35,463 --> 01:09:37,257
TRUE TO LOVE

944
01:09:37,340 --> 01:09:39,467
-Bo-ra!
-Don't go.

945
01:09:39,551 --> 01:09:40,468
What are you saying?

946
01:09:40,552 --> 01:09:43,638
A clingy ex who talks about
revenge or lingering love.

947
01:09:43,722 --> 01:09:45,640
She just wants to see her ex
regret it and cry.

948
01:09:45,724 --> 01:09:46,683
Did she say that?

949
01:09:46,766 --> 01:09:49,269
-That I two-timed and moved on right away?
-She didn't.

950
01:09:49,352 --> 01:09:50,937
Weren't you going with Su-hyeok?

951
01:09:51,021 --> 01:09:51,938
I don't know.

952
01:09:52,022 --> 01:09:53,398
-He ran away.
-Hi, Ju-wan.

953
01:09:53,481 --> 01:09:55,150
-Ju-wan's here.
-Where's she going?

954
01:09:55,233 --> 01:09:56,943
Isn't she going to
go head-to-head with Ju-wan?

955
01:09:57,652 --> 01:09:58,862
Where were you at dawn?

956
01:09:58,945 --> 01:10:00,864
-You were not in bed.
-You think she knows?

957
01:10:00,947 --> 01:10:02,407
She sensed something's off.

958
01:10:02,490 --> 01:10:05,035
So, from now on,
you shouldn't come downstairs.

959
01:10:05,118 --> 01:10:07,162
So what's going on with you and Bo-ra?

960
01:10:07,245 --> 01:10:08,914
There is something going on.

961
01:10:08,997 --> 01:10:11,917
I don't want you to get hurt anymore.

962
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:13,251
Don't worry about me.

963
01:10:13,335 --> 01:10:15,837
-Cute.
-He is a very good man.

964
01:10:15,921 --> 01:10:17,547
I like Bo-ra a lot.
